{
  "texts": [
    "For routine transformations, strains were made competent for chemical transformation.",
    "Five milliliters of an overnight culture of DH10B cells was subcultured into 500 mL LB medium and grown at 37 °C and 250 r.p.m.",
    "until an optical density of 0.7 was reached (~3 h).",
    "Cultures were centrifuged (3500 × g, 4 °C, 10 min), and pellets were washed with 70 mL chemical competence buffer (10% glycerol, 100 mM CaCl 2) and centrifuged again (3500 × g, 4 °C, 10 min).",
    "The resulting pellets were resuspended in 20 mL chemical competence buffer."
  ]
}